  "body": "\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI have already solc installed via npm , and install truffle . how should truffle detect it ?\r\n\r\nwhen i run truffle compile it is trying to connect to internet to download solc and then cached it.\r\n\r\nBut i don't want truffle to behave like that because like i said . i've already a solc installed.\r\n\r\nAny suggesstion?\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\ntruffle obtain solc 0.5.11\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nwill cached the solc that was already installed via npm not from truffle\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nIt connects to solc-bin through internet.\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Windows 7 \r\n\r\n* Truffle version 5.0.36\r\n* node version v10.16.3:\r\n* npm version 6.9.0\r\n",
